OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWelsh language oath asks   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpeople to curse at God     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A citizenship oath written in Welsh has
OL,6, been criticised for an error asking    
OL,7, people to literally curse at God.      
OL,9,FWales' education minister Jeremy Miles 
OL,10,Fsays he will write to the UK government
OL,11,Fto remind them to use the language     
OL,12,Faccurately.                            
OL,14,FIt comes after an emergency mobile text
OL,15,Falert in Welsh used a made-up word.    
OL,17,FThe Home Office, which produced the    
OL,18,Foath of allegiance, said it recognises 
OL,19,Fthe "importance" of correct            
OL,20,Ftranslation.                           
